After years of anticipation, James Gunn's Superman (2025) has finally arrived—and we have a lot to say. In this epic 4-hour+ episode, the Major Issues crew breaks down every heroic moment, shocking twist, and bold creative decision that sets this film apart from previous incarnations of the Man of Steel. From David Corenswet's debut as Clark Kent to the introduction of DCU's new tone and direction, we leave no stone unturned. How does it stack up against past Superman films? Did Gunn stick the landing? And what does this mean for the future of the DC Universe? Strap in, grab a snack, and join us for our most super-sized conversation yet! 💥🦅👓

Please leave us a review on [ITunes](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us wherever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by ComicBook Clique, the only stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.

